arXiv:2503.08618v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: {In 2020, Carney et.al. proved the quaternionic version of the Enestr"{o}m-Kakeya Theorem, which states that a polynomial $p(q)=\sum_{
u=0}^n q^
u a_
u$ with non-negative and monotonically increasing coefficients $(0<a_0\le a_1\le \cdots \le a_n)$ has all of its zeros within the unit ball $|q|\le 1$. Numerous generalizations of Enestr"{o}m-Kakeya Theorem are available in the literatures (\cite{m}-\cite{mmr}). In this paper, we extend some of these generalizations to the quaternionic context and present several potential results.}
